[09:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'or colors of stuff in the scene if you want. So, here\'s how it works. Gen Recon takes a set of images or frames in a video and then it generates chunks of the 3D scene together so that the full'

[09:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'scene stays consistent. It also uses Trellis 2 as what they call a generative shape prior. So, think of this as like giving the system a strong sense of what real 3D shapes should look like instead'

[09:57] [scene:talk]
